Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?feat:=20M2=20=E2=80=94=20auto-fill=20'holiday'?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20attendance=20+=20exclude=20from=20%?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The 'holidays' table existed and the dashboard read it, but attendance
records weren't being created on declared holidays. Everyone showed as
"unmarked" — and even when admin manually marked 'holiday', the
attendance % treated those days as absent because the denominator was
total instead of working_days.

Two parts:

1. New artisan command 'attendance:fill-holidays'
   php artisan attendance:fill-holidays                        # today
   php artisan attendance:fill-holidays --date=2026-04-26
   php artisan attendance:fill-holidays --school=3 --days=30   # backfill 30 days
   php artisan attendance:fill-holidays --force                # overwrite

   For each declared Holiday in the date range, creates a 'holiday'
   row for every active student and active staff in that school.
   Idempotent — uses updateOrCreate. Won't overwrite existing
   non-holiday rows unless --force. Multi-day holidays (date..end_date)
   are expanded to one row per day.

2. Daily schedule (routes/console.php)
   Schedule::command('attendance:fill-holidays')->dailyAt('00:30')
       ->withoutOverlapping();

   Runs early so the rows exist before anyone opens the dashboard or
   mark page on a holiday morning.

3. Attendance % now excludes holidays from the denominator
   (present + late*0.5 + half_day*0.5) / (total - holiday)

   Touched four mobile API summary builders:
     MobileApiController::attendance() teacher branch
     MobileApiController::attendance() student/parent branch
     MobileApiController::stats() — parent dashboard tile
     MobileApiController::attendanceSummary() — dashboard widget
     Api/Mobile/AttendanceController.php
   All now return 'holiday' and 'working_days' alongside the existing
   present/absent/late/half_day/leave breakdown.

Prerequisites: the enum migration from the previous commit
(2026_04_27_114325_add_holiday_to_attendance_status_enum) — without it
the inserts would fail with truncation errors.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
